blog.name: kippen-goodman-stan
blog.title: Tyrus!!!
blog.description: Of course I came

body:
50 days of Andi Mack

Season 2 Episode 4: Mama

  • OK, I need to learn Bex’s rubix cube song asap
  • Oh God, fidget spinners. That did not age well
  • “How do you say doshus magoshus in Hebrew?” Omigod Jonah just stop
  • OK, I’m all for self deprecating humour, but when Cyrus does it I just want to hug him and let him know how perfect he is
  • “You can sign me up when you find a food service that delivers baby taters and milkshakes” That woman is so going to be me when I’m older
  • I love the early 2000s vibe in the flashbacks with Bex and Cece
  • “I’ve lost my friends, I’ve lost my family, I’ve lost my teeth. But I have never lost a game” Well that’s… surprisingly morbid
  • That skateboard scene was perfect “You’re one of a kind Cyrus” “You and me? Skateboard buddies? I want that!”
  • I love how Jonah immediately calls an ambulance without even checking on Cyrus
  • I love the dynamic between Buffy and that old woman
  • “Sometimes I forget how hopeless he is” “You do?!” “It’s his defining characteristic!“ Whoah whoah whoah! Hold on, they are supposed to be his friends right? No wonder Cyrus’ self esteem is so low
  • "Have fun. I’ll just be singing to this cube” Why is this such a mood?

summary: Something to keep an eye on: There are recently-added listings that imply that Disney Channel will be airing re-runs of Andi...
caption:
Something to keep an eye on:

There are recently-added listings that imply that Disney Channel will be airing re-runs of Andi Mack from the beginning starting on May 28 at midnight. Most of these episodes were previously pulled from the lineup because of the Westmoreland’s arrest. 

In the past, listings have accidentally listed these episodes and then the episodes that ultimately air have ended up being different ones or the listing will change closer to the date - so there’s no guarantee that these will actually air, but I think it’s worth keeping an eye on. 

I’ve been wondering if Disney would do anything “special” leading up to the finale in July, and if these listings end up being correct - it’s looking like they could be planning to air all of the past episodes before the finale airs. If they start with episode one on May 28 and air one episode per day, that should give them just enough time to air all 56 episodes (and possibly the cast party special) before July 26. I’m also holding out hope that they’ll put all of the episodes back on DisneyNOW in June or July for people to stream leading up to the finale.

Obviously this is all just speculation, and the listings could be changed at any time or they could not change, but the episode that airs could still be different than what the listings say right now. Even if they do start airing these older episodes, it doesn’t necessarily mean they will do anything special leading up to the premiere or make the episodes available online again so don’t take anything I’ve said as fact. I just noticed this while waiting for the new episode descriptions and thought it was interesting.
